'''Congenital dyserythropoietic anemia type II''' (CDA II), or HEMPAS is a rare genetic anemia in humans characterized by hereditary erythroblastic multinuclearity with positive acidified serum lysis test.<ref name=pmid8043936>{{cite journal |pmid=8043936 |year=1993 |last1=Fukuda |first1=Michiko N. |title=Congenital dyserythropoietic anaemia type II (HEMPAS) and its molecular basis |volume=6 |issue=2 |pages=493–511 |journal=Baillière's Clinical Haematology |doi=10.1016/S0950-3536(05)80156-8}}</ref>

