==Description==
The anemia associated with CDA type II can range from mild to severe, and most affected individuals have jaundice, hepatosplenomegaly, and the formation of hard deposits in the gallbladder called bilirubin gallstones. This form of the disorder is usually diagnosed in adolescence or early adulthood. An abnormal buildup of iron typically occurs after age 20, leading to complications including heart disease, diabetes, and cirrhosis.<ref name="bare_url" />

==Treatment==
Treatment consists of frequent [[blood transfusions]] and [[chelation therapy]]. Potential cures include [[bone marrow transplantation]] and [[gene therapy]].

